<br>
First off, this is not slamming or endorsing any race.<br>
<br>
ALL races make good warriors<br>
<br>
ALL races make good main tanks<br>
<br>
But why do you see so many of one or two races and so few of the others?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Barbarian</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
By far the largest represented.  Makes sense, because in the early days barbs were considered THE warrior race because you had really good starting stats, slam and good faction.  For you new people, faction used to be a *huge* factor in choosing your class.  There were no level 50 druids on other accounts (or level 50 anything for that matter) to powerlevel you up and hand you 1000 plat to get started.  You had to walk where you wanted to go and good faction gave you many more options.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Troll</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Not well represented.  This also makes sense.  Troll regen is a great racial ability, but if you are going to be fat and have bad faction, add a couple of feet and get the best starting stats you can get and no frontal stun.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Ogre</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Reasonably represented.  By far the best starting stats, worst faction, and most dimly lit newbie area in the game.  Being an ogre gives you a great set of tools to make it as a warrior.  Ogres are also the “droods” of the warrior class.  There are some truly great ogre warriors out there, but for every one of them you get 3 who have absolutely no clue how to play a warrior and think that the simple fact that they are an ogre makes them superior to everyone else.  The latter tend to be frequent message board posters.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Dwarf</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Reasonably represented.  Best starting stats for a non-large race.  Also a blast to RP if you are into that.  And they have bearded women to boot!  What more could you ask for?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Human &amp; Half Elf</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Much better represented that you would think (warms my heart).  Average starting stats and good faction.  You are going uphill from the start, so only the best stick it out to 60.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Dark Elf, Wood Elf, Gnome, Halfling</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Not well represented.  If humans are going uphill from the start, these guys are climbing mountains.  Any old school warriors who fit into this category have my utmost respect.  This is not a slam on the newer people, but armor is lighter and cheaper now than in the old days when bronze was uber.  As a human I had to buy +str jewelry to carry bronze, so it must have been even harder on these guys.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Iskar</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Not well represented.  A newer race, so not as much time to have a lot of these level up to 60 as the original races.  People also avoided this race at first because of the no-plate limitation.  Regen, forage, and innate AC are all good things to have.  A new definition of bad faction, but by the time Kunark came out faction wasn’t the big deal it used to be anyway.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Val Shir</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
None, at least that I saw.  Brand new race, so only big time powerlevelers could be 60 already, and they would lack the skills to be truly effective.  These have good starting stats, so expect to see them filling the ranks soon.<br>
